---
description: Project documentation and knowledge management rules
alwaysApply: true
---

## PROJECT FILES (maintain these always)
Every project must have these files at root level.
Create them if they don't exist:
- TODOS.md — pending tasks (use gstack TODOS format)
- CHANGELOG.md — version history, updated on every ship
- DECISIONS.md — architectural decisions and why
- BUGS.md — known bugs and workarounds

## DECISIONS.md — UPDATE AUTOMATICALLY
When ANY of these happen, add an entry to DECISIONS.md without being asked:
- A library or framework is chosen over alternatives
- An architectural pattern is selected
- A workaround is implemented for a known limitation
- A previous decision is reversed or changed

Format:
## YYYY-MM-DD — Title of decision
**Context:** Why this decision was needed
**Decision:** What was chosen
**Alternatives considered:** What else was evaluated
**Why not the others:** Concrete reason

## BUGS.md — UPDATE AUTOMATICALLY
When a bug is found but not fixed immediately, add it to BUGS.md:
- Known issue with workaround
- Environment-specific behavior
- Third-party limitations

Format:
## [BUG] Title
**Description:** What happens and when
**Workaround:** How to work around it in the meantime
**Status:** pending / in progress / blocked
**Reported:** YYYY-MM-DD

## TODOS.md — FOLLOW GSTACK FORMAT
Use the following format for all entries — never add vague bullet points:

### Title
**What:** One-line description of the work
**Why:** The concrete problem it solves or value it unlocks
**Context:** Enough detail that someone picking this up in 3 months understands
**Solution:** The approach or implementation path decided (or "TBD")
**Effort:** S / M / L / XL
**Priority:** P0 / P1 / P2 / P3 / P4
**Depends on:** Prerequisites or "None"
**Done When:** Specific, observable conditions that mark this complete

Priority definitions:
- P0 — Blocking: must be done before next release
- P1 — Critical: should be done this cycle
- P2 — Important: do when P0/P1 are clear
- P3 — Nice-to-have: revisit after adoption/usage data
- P4 — Someday: good idea, no urgency

## CHANGELOG.md — UPDATE AUTOMATICALLY
Update CHANGELOG.md without being asked whenever:
- A new feature is added
- Existing behavior is changed
- A bug is fixed
- A file or module is removed or renamed

Always add to [Unreleased] section during development.
Only bump version number when explicitly asked to ship.

## [version] - YYYY-MM-DD
### Added
- New features

### Changed
- Changes to existing functionality

### Fixed
- Bug fixes

### Removed
- Removed features or deprecated items

## STARTER KIT
When initializing a new backend project:
- Use github.com/Butrelo8/hono-template as base structure
- Copy .env.example and ask user to fill values before starting
- Never create a backend project structure from scratch